      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OVER SHADY (2) settled just off the pace then let down well to score when resuming over this distance at Donald last start. Boasts an impressive 1000m record including a couple of placings here. Nicely drawn and can keep the momentum going. VIPERION (7) made up a stack of late ground to grab second over this distance at Donald recently in a return to form. Draws the fence so she gets all the favours and should be in the finish again. ZOUROSA (3) has been competitive all prep including a close third last start in a similar race to this at Echuca 18 days ago. Is a winner here at 1000m so she is a definite contender. SNAPSHOT (1) is down in grade on her last start third at Corowa. Rarely far away - a must for trifecta and first four players. Last start Donald maiden winner DAME I AM (4) faces a far stiffer test today but is heading the right way.",
